# GPT-2 MLA + RA Comprehensive Ablation
#
# Tests all MLA variants with and without reciprocal attention:
#   MLA0       - GPT2_MLA: MLA only (TL-cache latent compression)
#   MLAKV0     - GPT2_MLA_KV: MLA + learned KVSplice compression
#   MLAKV20    - GPT2_MLA_KV2: Separate K/V latents (no shared TL-cache)
#   MLAKV2M0   - GPT2_MLA_KV2M: K/V latents + MLP compression
#   RAMLA0     - GPT2_MLA_RA: MLA + reciprocal attention (RALATE pattern)
#   RAMLAKV0   - GPT2_MLA_RA_KV: RA + MLA + learned KVSplice compression
#   RAMLAKVM0  - GPT2_MLA_RA_KVM: RA + MLA + KV + MLP compression (full stack)
#
# RALATE pattern: layers 0-5 standard, layers 6-11 reciprocal (fixed at init).
# All MLA variants use d_latent=256 for consistent compression ratio.
# KVSplice uses compression_ratio=0.5 (further 2x compression beyond MLA).
#
# This ablation measures:
# - Impact of MLA latent compression on quality
# - Benefit of reciprocal attention for MLA architectures
# - Effect of learned KVSplice compression
# - Trade-offs of MLP compression combined with attention compression
#
# All use standard LR (6e-4) for fair comparison.

CONFIG_MODEL_MODE_SINGLE=y
CONFIG_MODEL_SELECT_GPT2=y
CONFIG_MODEL_GPT2=y
CONFIG_MODEL="gpt2"

